        </h3>

        <p>Music itself follows a set of rules to help oversee the incorporation of varying tone harmonics via defining specific sound waves played at particular orders and times. An example of this is shown below being Mozart's rendition of Jane Taylor's <em>"Twinkle Twinkle Little Star"</em>. For the sake of simplicity, this document will focus on defining sound waves via mathematics and physics versus the exploration of musicology. </p>

